					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-781289#post-2116556</guid>
				<title>interesting</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-781289/scp-2021#post-2116556</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 23 Sep 2014 15:02:15 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Retoxe</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1655146</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>i really like the concept.</p> <p>i wonder what could happen if two people stood on the sides of a large, composite paper, and the person who can see the other 'through' the reverse side, reached in and tired to pull out the person facing the obverse (real) side.</p> <p>Since the person reaching 'through' the paper isn't actually going to touch the real person standing on the other side, will that affect him at all? Would he be able to pull it out?</p> <p>Also, an interesting note, the paper seems to allow for infinite duplication of items (well, assuming the 'pulled out' items are just as real and hold same properties). So, someone should perhaps try to replicate, say, SCP-500?</p> <p>Place pill on table, paper facing reverse side to test subject/obverse side to pill. Subject reaches in, pulls pill out. Now we have original + copy in our reality. Reach around paper, and place copy pill next to original. Should show up when viewed through reverse of paper - reach in and grab a copy of a copy. Hm. Copy of a copy only screams 'corruption' to me&#8230;</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
