					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-781289#post-1976803</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-781289/scp-2021#post-1976803</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 25 Feb 2014 00:55:14 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zolgamax</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1707551</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>These sheets of paper are quite literally one-sided. As in, one side doesn't exist, and is just an empty patch of air.</p> <p>&#8230;Except things that pass through the &quot;empty&quot; patch of air don't come out the other side of the sheet, they just seem to vanish &quot;into&quot; it. The Foundation dropped a hamster into it, and now it's gone. Then, a D-Class reached through the sheet and picked up a beaker on the other side.</p> <p>&#8230;Except his arm still didn't go &quot;through&quot; the sheet, and now the Foundation has two beakers, one of which didn't exist before. Plus, the D-Class says that his arm feels strange, and there's a weird smell coming from where he reached through. Perhaps the smell&#8230;</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Spoiler/Theory</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide&nbsp;me</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>of a rotting arm, somehow severed and left to sit between dimensions?</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
